20 WHEREAS, Elizabeth "Betty" Kaufman Thines was born in the rural
21 community of St. Vincent, Arkansas, on March 4, 1918; and
22
23 WHEREAS, Elizabeth "Betty" Kaufman Thines worked alongside eight (8) of
24 her siblings to take over operation of Kaufman Farms in 1931, and they were
25 selected as the 1939 Arkansas landowner champions of the Plant to Prosper
26 Competition, which recognized farmers who incorporated best farming practices
27 and improved utilization of cotton cropland; and
28
29 WHEREAS, Elizabeth "Betty" Kaufman Thines served as Deputy County Clerk
30 in Conway County, Arkansas, from 1941-45; and
31
32 WHEREAS, Elizabeth "Betty" Kaufman Thines was a stenographer and
33 secretary for the House of Representatives during 1953-55 and 1959; and
34
35 WHEREAS, during her time of service to the House of Representatives in
36 Arkansas, Elizabeth "Betty" Kaufman Thines lived and worked in Vermont, but
